01:44.077 --> 01:55.794
In John chapter 13, verse 1, leading into the account of Jesus washing the feet of His disciples, John says, when His hour drew near,

01:57.090 --> 02:02.037
to depart out of this world to his father, having loved his own who were in the world.

02:02.337 --> 02:04.660
He loved them to the end.

02:06.262 --> 02:12.370
This God-man who so clearly pursued his father's glory throughout his life, John says, loved his own.

02:14.072 --> 02:15.034
It's not in competition.

02:16.015 --> 02:24.306
He was able to love his own, his disciples, his people, because he loved his father's glory and he loved him to the end.

02:24.642 --> 02:38.259
And so John 1334, the great love command has as it's standard, as it's grounding Jesus' love for his people, which is exhibited at the cross.

02:39.200 --> 02:47.630
A new commandment I give you that you love one another, here's the key, just as I have loved you.

02:49.252 --> 02:50.934
